column3: "find a way so that x can have 3 in a row with open spaces to each side"
"I try to comprise the best possible position that the most x have an opportunity to win."
"I first needed to force X into a situation where it would have three in a ow with two openings. I then followed that force to a win."
"I looked to see where I could put the x where there were two ends available"

"I had it the first time I did it, but I did not look to see which one I had done first, I just went with my gut. I then had to redo the board and start over, then after reading the directions again, I was also playing for O to win, that made a difference."
"I chose the box that seemed to offer the most options. This turned out to be the one."
"i thought that if i placed the x there, it would force o to place on the far right end"
"I worked through the board to see what would work"
"Just looked at all the possible moves until the right one popped out"
"Using B4 I was able to have a move that would ensure a win no matter what O did. I kept an open square for 3 possible wins."
"I couldn't figure it out, so I just tried my best guess, but I don't think it's correct."
"I tried to set up a win from the corner. However, I notice that o is set up to win a few ways too. "

"I forced O to block me repeatedly rather than make progress towards connecting 4 of it's own, until I had a spot open where I could win in two different directions. This resulted in a guaranteed win because O can't block both moves on one turn."
"that was the easiest way for x to win"
"I tried to create a situation where I would always have an opening on either side."
"I ensured that there were 3 Xs in a row with open spaces on both sides."
"I tried to help x win with as little moves as possible. Getting 3 x's together with a space on each side would do that."

"I just ran through every potential placement of circle, even the moves that would be precognizant of what I was doing, and after testing them all, it seemed pretty clear cut that circle could not win. When I couldn't find a solution for circle, I made my choices and stuck with it."
"Force opponents to move certain spots while creating opening for yourself "

"C4 has 2 adjacent X's. This grants two ways to push for a win. Both possible directions are open-ended(they aren't block on either side). This means O need to guard 4 spots to prevent a loss. X only needs 3 turns to win after his move on C4. As such, O simply does not have enough moves left to guard all spots and prevent a win."
"I went with what gave x more movement options "
"i tried playing through the game and that was the only solution i found personally"
"I tried to make it so I had an opportunity to go either horizontal or diagonally without the other player blocking me."
"I tried to block O from moving to complete a row."
"I tried to find spots where O would be forced to place a mark to prevent me from winning on the next turn so I could control where they placed their marks"
"I just played around a bit, and kind of accidentally found a spot where if I make a move there, I'm gonna win no matter what O does."
"I tried to look at all aspects as to how o could win. I noticed that o would try to win on the diagonal and setup my x pieces to provide 2 main outs."
"just making it so there are multiple possibilities "
"I couldn't solve it. I tried various starting points and played the game as normal. I didn't use any special strategy."
"I didn't have any strategy except played how I would normally play as X"
"I found a way to manipulate O's next move on each turn, so that by the 4th turn, O could not block both path's to an X win. "
"I just kept trying my hardest to beat the other side until I found the spot where X wins for sure"
"I wanted to try to get 3 in a row with open ends on the board, in the space I picked I can get that no matter what happens. "
"I tried to open up more places I could get 4 in a row by placing an X that would allow me to put more connecting in more than one direction."
"Tried to get 4 in a row in as least turns as possible for x"
"it worked where x won even when o was trying"
"I just looked for any way to put O into a situation where they could not block X."
"I tried a number of different strategies until I found a no-win situation for O"
"by playing at c3, x has multiple avenues to win and keep the opponent on the defensive."
"I tried to put the x nearby the others to use those as part of the win and get the x's in a row of three with two blanks on the either side"
"You need to expand on two spaces already given to you in a way that gives you two ways to win."
"It seemed to make sense since that spot can set up a number of win conditions while also blocking a potential win from the other player"
"I looked at the board and tried to find places where there were multiple play options. Then I tried to find places where I could win several ways."
